{"symbol": "SGF29", "uniprot": "Q96ES7", "protein_name": "SAGA-associated factor 29", "length": 293, "function": "Chromatin reader component of some histone acetyltransferase (HAT) SAGA-type complexes like the TFTC-HAT, ATAC or STAGA complexes (PubMed:19103755, PubMed:20850016, PubMed:21685874, PubMed:26421618, PubMed:26578293). SGF29 specifically recognizes and binds methylated 'Lys-4' of histone H3 (H3K4me), with a preference for trimethylated form (H3K4me3) (PubMed:20850016, PubMed:21685874, PubMed:26421618, PubMed:26578293). In the SAGA-type complexes, SGF29 is required to recruit complexes to H3K4me (PubMed:20850016). Involved in the response to endoplasmic reticulum (ER) stress by recruiting the SAGA complex to H3K4me, thereby promoting histone H3 acetylation and cell survival (PubMed:23894581). Also binds non-histone proteins that are methylated on Lys residues: specifically recognizes and binds CGAS monomethylated on 'Lys-506' (By similarity)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000176476", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.1449, "protein_drug": 0.753, "rna_drug": 0.341}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": false, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "Small molecule", "winning_axis": "protein", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.966", "sirna_score": "0.248", "aso_score": "0.24"}, "modality": "Small molecule", "structure": "data/structures/SGF29.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.321, "volume": 546.1, "residues": [78, 81, 82, 84, 85, 88, 129, 131, 132, 133, 134, 135, 136, 139, 216]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.16, "volume": 855.7, "residues": [95, 99, 104, 105, 106, 108, 110, 111, 112, 113, 114, 179, 193, 194, 195, 197, 200]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.146, "volume": 568.7, "residues": [238, 241, 245, 264, 265, 266, 267, 272, 273]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q96ES7"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": 